carGeneral:meta.pressText: The Opel Astra is a compact car (C-segment) engineered and manufactured by the German automaker Opel since 1991.
The Honda Civic is a line of cars manufactured by Honda. Originally a subcompact, the Civic has gone through several generational changes.
The BMW 3 Series is a compact executive car manufactured by the German automaker BMW since May 1975.
The Tesla Model S is a battery-powered liftback car serving as the flagship model of Tesla, Inc.
The Volkswagen Golf is a compact car:small family car produced by the German automotive manufacturer Volkswagen since 1974.
The Mazda3 or Mazda 3 is a compact car manufactured by Mazda, a Japanese automaker.
The Audi A4 is a line of compact executive cars produced since 1994 by the German car manufacturer Audi.
The Toyota Corolla is a series of compact cars manufactured and marketed globally by Toyota Motor Corporation.
The BMW X3 is a compact luxury crossover SUV manufactured by German automaker BMW since 2003.
The Ford Mustang is a series of American automobiles manufactured by Ford. In continuous production since 1964.
The Tesla Model 3 is a battery electric mid-size sedan with a fastback body style built by Tesla, Inc.
The Range Rover Sport is a mid-size luxury SUV produced by British manufacturer Land Rover.
The Kia Sportage is a compact SUV manufactured by the South Korean automaker Kia since 1993.
The Hyundai Tucson is a compact crossover SUV produced by the South Korean manufacturer Hyundai since 2004.
The Porsche 911 is a two-door, 2+2 high performance rear-engined sports car introduced in September 1964 by Porsche AG.
The Volkswagen Tiguan is a compact crossover vehicle manufactured by German automaker Volkswagen.
The Fiat 500 is a city car produced by the Italian manufacturer Fiat since 2007.
The Mini Cooper is a small economy car produced by the British Motor Corporation and its successors.
The Toyota RAV4 is a compact crossover SUV produced by the Japanese automobile manufacturer Toyota.
The Mercedes-Benz C-Class is a line of compact executive cars produced by Mercedes-Benz Group AG.
The BMW M3 is a high-performance version of the BMW 3 Series, developed by BMW's in-house motorsport division, BMW M GmbH.
The Chevrolet Corvette is a two-door, two-passenger sports car manufactured and marketed by Chevrolet since 1953.
The Audi Q5 is a series of compact luxury crossover SUVs produced by the German luxury car manufacturer Audi.
The Nissan Leaf is a compact five-door hatchback battery electric vehicle produced by Nissan.
The Ferrari F8 Tributo is a mid-engine sports car produced by the Italian automobile manufacturer Ferrari.
The Lamborghini Huracán is a sports car manufactured by Italian automotive manufacturer Lamborghini.
The BMW i3 is a B-segment, high-roof hatchback manufactured and marketed by BMW with an electric powertrain.
The Renault Clio is a supermini car, produced by French automobile manufacturer Renault.
The Peugeot 208 is a supermini car produced by the French manufacturer Peugeot.
The Škoda Octavia is a small family car produced by the Czech car manufacturer Škoda Auto since 1996.
The Volvo XC60 is a compact luxury crossover SUV manufactured and marketed by Swedish automaker Volvo Cars since 2008.
The Subaru Impreza is a compact car manufactured by the Japanese automaker Subaru since 1992.
The Jaguar XE is a compact executive car manufactured by British automotive company Jaguar Land Rover.
The Citroën C3 is a supermini car produced by French manufacturer Citroën since 2002.
The Saab 9-3 is a compact executive car produced by the Swedish automaker Saab Automobile.
The Toyota Camry is an automobile sold internationally by the Japanese auto manufacturer Toyota since 1982.
The Jeep Grand Cherokee is a range of mid-size SUVs produced by the American manufacturer Jeep.
The Acura TLX is a four-door entry-level luxury sedan sold by Acura, a luxury division of Honda.
The Porsche Cayenne is a mid-size luxury crossover SUV produced by the German manufacturer Porsche since 2002.
The Audi TT is a 2-door production sports car made by Audi since 1998, and currently in its third generation.
The Volkswagen Passat is a series of large family cars manufactured and marketed by Volkswagen since 1973.
The Mercedes-Benz E-Class is a range of executive cars manufactured by German automaker Mercedes-Benz.
The BMW 5 Series is an executive car manufactured and marketed by BMW since 1972.

The Hyundai Sonata is a mid-size car that has been manufactured by Hyundai since 1985.
The Kia Optima is a mid-size car manufactured by Kia since 2000.
The Nissan Rogue is a compact crossover SUV produced by the Japanese automaker Nissan.
The Nissan Altima is a mid-size car that has been manufactured by Nissan since 1992.
The Mazda CX-5 is a compact crossover SUV produced by Mazda since 2012.

The Honda Accord is a series of automobiles manufactured by Honda since 1976.
The Toyota Corolla Hybrid combines efficient hybrid technology with the reliability of the Corolla nameplate.
The Audi A6 is an executive car made by the German automaker Audi, now in its fifth generation.
